{"lemma":"إِبْرِيقِ","slug":"إِبْرِيقِ","root":"#.ب.ر.ق","root_slug":"_-ب-ر-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ب-ر-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2332"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A5%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%82%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pitcher, jug","examples":[{"text":"يَطُوفُ عَلَيْهِمْ وِلْدَانٌ مُّخَلَّدُونَ بِأَكْوَابٍ وَأَبَارِيقَ وَكَأْسٍ مِّن مَّعِينٍ","english":"There will circulate among them young boys made eternal, with beakers, pitchers and a glass of spring water."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Middle Persian or Parthian *ābrēk possibly via Classical Syriac ܐܒܪܝܩܐ (ʾaḇrēqā), attested as Classical Persian آبریز (ābrēz) from آب (āb, “water”) + the present stem of the verb ریختن (rēxtan, “to pour”). Compare Northern Kurdish avrêjk (“ewer”)."},"ipa":["/ʔib.riːq/","/ʔib.riːɡ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2332","headword_ar":"اـِبْرِيقٌ","root":"brq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a Persian word, (S, Msb,) arabicized, (S, Msb, K,) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=bo riyzo","text_ar":"ا=بْ رِيزْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(CK [in a MS. copy of the K and in the TA, incorrectly,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=b riy","text_ar":"ا=ب رِي"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A ewer, such as is used for wine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is used for water to be poured on the hands; each having a long and slender spout, and a handle;] a well-known vessel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vessel having a spout"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, and Bd and Jel in lvi. 18)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and a handle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd and Jel ibid:) accord. to Kr, a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwz","text_ar":"كُوز"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and so says AHn in one place; but in another he says that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kwz","text_ar":"كوز"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"somewhat like a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kwz","text_ar":"كوز"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the addition of a spout:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaAriyqu","text_ar":"اَبَارِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) [and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaAriqapN","text_ar":"اَبَارِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"].       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sword such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~aAq","text_ar":"بَرَّاق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) i. e. (TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sword that shines, gleams,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glistens, much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intensely:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Kr:) or simply a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sword:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) or it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bow in which are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talaAmiyE","text_ar":"تَلَامِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or places differing in colour from the rest, and,"},{"kind":"text","text":"app.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glistening"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) thus, accord. to Az, in a verse of ' Amr Ibn-Ahmar: but correctly, accord. to Sgh, it has there the first of the significations explained in this sentence: and it is said, also, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayofN A_iboriyqN","text_ar":"سَيْفٌ اـِبْرِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sword having much lustre, and much diversified with wavy marks"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streaks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in its grain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman who is beautiful, and splendid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brilliant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, JK, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in colour"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complexion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Lh, TA:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who shows her beauty intentionally."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~aAqapN","text_ar":"بَرَّاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~aAqN","text_ar":"بَرَّاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":").]"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","Kr","JK","Lh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}